    <item>
      <title>Installation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/installation/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/installation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;maven-dependencies&#34;&gt;Maven Dependencies&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Crest is split into two artifacts: the runtime and the API. Add both to your &lt;code&gt;pom.xml&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-xml&#34; data-lang=&#34;xml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;org.tomitribe&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;tomitribe-crest&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/dependency&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;org.tomitribe&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;tomitribe-crest-api&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#7ee787&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/dependency&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;tomitribe-crest-api&lt;/code&gt; artifact contains the annotations (&lt;code&gt;@Command&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;@Option&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;@Default&lt;/code&gt;, etc.) and interfaces your code compiles against. The &lt;code&gt;tomitribe-crest&lt;/code&gt; artifact is the runtime that discovers commands, parses arguments, and invokes methods.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;maven-archetype&#34;&gt;Maven Archetype&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To scaffold a new Crest project quickly, use the Maven archetype:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mvn archetype:generate &lt;span style=&#34;color:#79c0ff&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    -DarchetypeGroupId&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;org.tomitribe &lt;span style=&#34;color:#79c0ff&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    -DarchetypeArtifactId&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;tomitribe-crest-archetype&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This generates a project with the correct dependencies, a sample command class, and a &lt;code&gt;Main&lt;/code&gt; entry point ready to run.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Maven Project Setup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/maven-setup/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/maven-setup/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Most projects already have a multi-module Maven structure with domain logic, services, and APIs. To add a CLI powered by Crest, create a dedicated module that pulls in your existing code and packages it as an executable.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;project-structure&#34;&gt;Project Structure&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A typical layout adds a &lt;code&gt;mytool-cli&lt;/code&gt; module alongside your existing modules:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;myproject/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  myproject-core/        # Domain logic, services&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  myproject-api/         # Shared interfaces&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  myproject-cli/         # CLI module (new)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    src/main/java/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;      com/example/cli/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        MyCommands.java  # @Command methods&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        MyLoader.java    # Loader implementation&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    pom.xml&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  pom.xml                # Parent POM&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;cli-module-pom&#34;&gt;CLI Module POM&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The CLI module&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;pom.xml&lt;/code&gt; has three parts: dependencies on Crest and your project modules, the shade plugin to create an uber jar, and the crest-maven-plugin to generate descriptors and create the executable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Your First Command</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/first-command/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/first-command/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;a-simple-hello-command&#34;&gt;A Simple Hello Command&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In Crest, a public method annotated with &lt;code&gt;@Command&lt;/code&gt; becomes a CLI command. The method name is the command name, and its parameters become the command&amp;rsquo;s options and arguments.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;org.tomitribe.crest.api.Command&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;org.tomitribe.crest.api.Default&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;org.tomitribe.crest.api.Option&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f0883e;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;HelloCommand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@Command&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;hello&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@Option&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@Default&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;World&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;name,&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;                        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@Option&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;greeting&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@Default&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;greeting)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;greeting&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;, &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;name&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;}&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This single class gives you a fully working CLI command with named options, default values, and automatic help generation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Entry Point</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/entry-point/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/entry-point/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-main-class&#34;&gt;The Main Class&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every Crest application needs an entry point that wires up command discovery and dispatches CLI arguments. The simplest approach uses the built-in &lt;code&gt;Main&lt;/code&gt; class:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;org.tomitribe.crest.Main&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f0883e;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;MyCli&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;args)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Exception&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Main&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;main&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Main();&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;        &lt;/span&gt;main.run(args);&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;}&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6e7681&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;When constructed with &lt;code&gt;new Main()&lt;/code&gt;, Crest discovers commands automatically via the ServiceLoader mechanism (described below). The &lt;code&gt;run()&lt;/code&gt; method parses the arguments, finds the matching command, and invokes it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Testing Commands</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/testing/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/crest/getting-started/testing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;testing-with-mainbuilder&#34;&gt;Testing with Main.builder()&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Crest commands are plain Java methods, but testing through the full CLI pipeline ensures that argument parsing, defaults, validation, and output all work correctly. The &lt;code&gt;Main.builder()&lt;/code&gt; API makes this straightforward by letting you run commands in-process without ServiceLoader discovery or &lt;code&gt;System.exit&lt;/code&gt; calls.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;capturing-output-with-printstring&#34;&gt;Capturing Output with PrintString&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;PrintString&lt;/code&gt; from &lt;code&gt;tomitribe-util&lt;/code&gt; to capture command output. Pass it to the builder via &lt;code&gt;out()&lt;/code&gt;, then assert against its contents after running the command:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
  </channel>
